```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id using operator<< (arithmetic type)
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores count as arithmetic type
        stream << static_cast<uint32_t>(scores.size());

        // Write scores using operator<< which internally calls write_container
        stream << scores;

        // Write metadata using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the buffer
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream using the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Call the packet's serialise method with the stream
    packet.serialise(stream);

    // Return the buffer containing serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **`serialise` method implementation**:
   - Uses `stream << packet_id` for arithmetic type serialization
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed(username)` adaptor for username with length prefix
   - Writes scores count as arithmetic type using `static_cast<uint32_t>`
   - Uses `stream << scores` which internally calls `write_container`
   - Uses `hexi::null_terminated(metadata)` for null-terminated string serialization

2. **`serialize_packet` function**:
   - Creates `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Creates `hexi::buffer_adaptor` wrapping the buffer
   - Creates `hexi::binary_stream` using the adaptor
   - Calls `packet.serialise(stream)` to perform serialization
   - Returns the populated buffer

3. **Namespace usage**: All Hexi components are properly qualified with `hexi::` namespace

This implementation follows the exact specifications provided, using the appropriate adaptors and serialization methods as documented in the reference materials.

