Based on the reference materials and detailed specifications, here's the complete implementation:

```cpp
#include <hexi/pmc/buffer_read_adaptor.h>
#include <hexi/pmc/buffer_write_adaptor.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

std::vector<uint8_t> write_and_read_data(const std::vector<uint8_t>& input_data) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create buffer_write_adaptor instance for the buffer
    hexi::pmc::buffer_write_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> writer(buffer);

    // Check available space with free() and write the input data
    if (writer.free() < input_data.size()) {
        // Resize buffer if needed to accommodate the data
        buffer.resize(input_data.size());
        // Reinitialize writer with the resized buffer
        writer = hexi::pmc::buffer_write_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>>(buffer);
    }

    writer.write(input_data.data(), input_data.size());

    // Create buffer_read_adaptor instance for the same buffer
    hexi::pmc::buffer_read_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> reader(buffer);

    // Check readable size with size() and read the data back
    std::vector<uint8_t> output_data(reader.size());
    reader.read(output_data.data(), output_data.size());

    return output_data;
}

std::vector<uint8_t> peek_data_without_advancing(std::vector<uint8_t>& buffer_data, std::size_t peek_size) {
    // Create buffer_read_adaptor instance for the provided buffer
    hexi::pmc::buffer_read_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> reader(buffer_data);

    // Use read_ptr() to get pointer to current read position
    const uint8_t* data_ptr = reader.read_ptr();

    // Use copy() to peek at data without advancing read pointer
    std::vector<uint8_t> peeked_data(peek_size);
    reader.copy(peeked_data.data(), peek_size);

    // Use read() to consume the data (advance read pointer)
    std::vector<uint8_t> consumed_data(peek_size);
    reader.read(consumed_data.data(), peek_size);

    return peeked_data;
}
```

**Key Implementation Details:**

1. **`write_and_read_data` function:**
   - Creates a `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Uses `buffer_write_adaptor` to write input data to the buffer
   - Checks available space using `free()` and resizes buffer if needed
   - Uses `buffer_read_adaptor` to read data back from the buffer
   - Returns the read data

2. **`peek_data_without_advancing` function:**
   - Takes a non-const reference to buffer_data (modified from original spec)
   - Uses `read_ptr()` to get pointer to current read position
   - Uses `copy()` to peek at data without advancing read pointer
   - Uses `read()` to consume the data (advance read pointer)
   - Returns the peeked data

**Note:** The second function parameter was changed from `const std::vector<uint8_t>&` to `std::vector<uint8_t>&` since `buffer_read_adaptor` requires a non-const reference to modify the read position.

